body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting our customer support. My name is Kyle Butler and I am from SecureRide Car Dealership. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, Marie. Can you please provide me with your phone number for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's nine three seven- five five five- eight two two one.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Marie. Can you also confirm the city you are currently located in?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information. Is there anything else you would like to add, Marie?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, I'm feeling frustrated with the security at your dealership.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Marie. We will address this promptly. Thank you for bringing it to our attention. We appreciate your time.
